    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Carpinus betulus, native to Europe, Asia, and Iran. It is used for piano actions, turnery, billiard cues, and violin bridges.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
